{
  "stem": "17299.2",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But on the way to-- between Berlin and Konigsberg, somewhere along the line, something went wrong with the train, and they had to take one of the cars out.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they pushed peoples in other cars, and we got some people, and they had to lie on the floor because there were no [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] place to sit for them.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Also, we had a problem because we were always sitting day and night.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "A lot of them had swelling in the legs because you could not move, and they had edemas in the legs.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, not all.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You could not leave the train at all.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We could open the window when-- and the train was heated, to our surprise.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And when we arrived somewhere in-- in Lithuania near Schaulen-- Siauliai I think it's in Estonian-- the train stopped, because there was only one train line, because it was a secondary or third train which was not important, because military trains had to go.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The Germans allowed us to get out of the train and to get some water since we did not have anything to drink anymore.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Also there was the problem that a number of toilets were blocked.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And then we were-- after the train left, it went up to Riga.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And when we arrived in Riga in the main railroad station, we had to sit there for two hours.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And then the train was taken out again and it was moved to Skirotava, which was outside of Riga, which had a military ramp which was used by the Latvian army for that purpose.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And we heard the-- the-- the engines were taking off, and within an hour or two everything was ice.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "It was bitter cold.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "At this time we didn't know anything.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
